SCHOOL OPERATIONS BLUEPRINT

(Ground truth for your Campus app)

This blueprint assumes:

Academic structures already exist (years, terms, classes, sections, subjects)

Admin screens already expose many things

User-facing screens are underpowered and under-connected

We are aligning, not rebuilding.

1Ô∏è‚É£ CORE PRINCIPLE (THIS FIXES EVERYTHING)

Your app must follow this rule:

Tables live in the database and admin tooling.
Users experience workflows, not tables.

So:

Admin ‚Üí sees structured tables, grids, controls

Staff / Students / Parents ‚Üí see forms, actions, states, timelines

This alone explains 70% of the ‚Äúit feels empty‚Äù problem.

