4Ô∏è‚É£ MODULE BLUEPRINTS (WHAT EACH MUST BECOME)
A) Dashboard (Critical Weak Spot)

Dashboard must show real data, not placeholders:

Admin Dashboard:

Total students (current academic year)

Attendance today

Pending admissions

Upcoming exams

Fee collection status

Recent announcements

Employee Dashboard:

Today‚Äôs classes

Pending grading

Announcements

Attendance tasks

Student / Parent Dashboard:

Today‚Äôs timetable

Assignments due

Attendance summary

Announcements

‚ùå If dashboard numbers are fake ‚Üí system feels fake.

B) Schedule (Timetable Engine, not a list)

Admin / Authorized Employee:

Create timetable via guided flow, not table dump:

Select year + term

Select class + section

Define days & time slots

Assign subject + employee + room

Validate conflicts

Publish / lock timetable

Users:

See weekly visual schedule

No editing

Filter by today / week

C) Assignments (Academic Workflow)

Assignment lifecycle:

Draft ‚Üí Published ‚Üí Submitted ‚Üí Reviewed ‚Üí Closed


Creation:

Employee selects class/section/subject

Adds instructions, deadline, max score

Optional file upload

Student:

Upload submission

View status

Employee:

Review

Score

Comment

Parent:

View progress (read-only)

D) Attendance (Daily Authority System)

Attendance is:

Per academic year

Per class / subject

Time-bound

Flow:

Employee opens today‚Äôs class

Marks attendance

Submit ‚Üí locked

Admin can audit/edit (with log)

Parents & students:

View summaries, not raw tables

E) Announcements (Institutional Communication)

Announcements must support:

Targeting:

Entire school

Role-based

Class/section-based

Priority

Optional expiry

Delivery:

In-app

Email (later)

Parent/student:

Read-only

Timestamped

Ordered by relevance

F) Users & Profiles (Missing Depth)

Profiles must support:

Avatar upload (Neon-stored public URL)

School logo upload

Role & sub-role visibility

Status (active, suspended, alumni)

Default avatar is fine ‚Äî but change must work end-to-end.

G) Files & Media

Store metadata in Neon

Files via Backblaze (private)

Public-facing images (logos, avatars) ‚Üí Neon URLs

No broken images, no placeholders

5Ô∏è‚É£ ADMIN AREA (WHERE TABLES BELONG)

Admin section is allowed to be:

Table-heavy

Dense

Powerful

But:

Every admin table must power a user-facing experience

No admin-only features that never surface to users

6Ô∏è‚É£ QUALITY CHECKS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

For every feature, verify:

Can data be created?

Can it be edited?

Is it visible to the correct roles?

Does it survive reload?

Is it scoped to academic year?

Is there a lifecycle/state?

If any answer is ‚Äúno‚Äù ‚Üí feature is incomplete.
