OPTION B ‚Äî MASTER PROMPT (Give This to the Dev / AI)

You asked for a single powerful prompt.
Here it is ‚Äî copy exactly as is üëá

üîπ MASTER CONTINUATION PROMPT

You are continuing development of a full School Management System (Eskooly-grade), not a demo or starter app.

Core rules:

Treat Teacher as a sub-role of Employee, not a primary role.

Support Admin, Employee (with multiple sub-roles), Student, Parent.

Assume real schools with principals, bursars, secretaries, etc.

Your task:

Audit existing DB schema, APIs, and UI for completeness ‚Äî not just existence.

Identify shallow or partially implemented features and fully develop them.

Replace table-only UI with proper form-based and card-based flows for end users.

Ensure dashboards show real aggregated data, not placeholders.

Implement school identity features (logo, profile, branding).

Enforce sequential school setup (profile ‚Üí academic structure ‚Üí people).

Execution rules:

Make decisions independently using best practices.

Do NOT stop after each step for confirmation.

Batch schema changes, push DB migrations once.

Implement API, UI, and permissions together.

Avoid token waste by continuing logically until a full domain is complete.

The goal is a production-ready SMS foundation, not incremental demos.
)

 MASTER EXECUTION PROMPT

You are continuing development of an existing School Management System (Campus).
This is NOT a prototype. This is a production-grade, Eskooly-level system.

IMPORTANT
- Your task is to COMPLETE, upgrade, CONNECT, and OPERATIONALIZE what exists.

CORE RULE:
Admin uses tables. Users experience workflows.

PRIMARY GOAL:
Turn all existing modules (dashboard, schedule, assignments, attendance, announcements, profiles)
into fully functional, role-aware, lifecycle-driven systems.


EXECUTION RULES:
- Always follow the School Data Spine (Academic Year ‚Üí Term ‚Üí Class ‚Üí Section ‚Üí Subject).
- No dummy data.
- No placeholder logic.
- No stopping for confirmation unless a system-breaking issue occurs.
- Push all schema changes.
- Wire backend to frontend immediately.
- Test end-to-end after each module.

MODULE PRIORITY ORDER:
1. Dashboard (real metrics)
2. Schedule (timetable engine)
3. Assignments (full lifecycle)
4. Attendance (daily authoritative record)
5. Announcements (targeted institutional communication)
6. Profiles, media, branding (avatars, logos)
etc

QUALITY BAR:
If a real school cannot operate daily using the feature, it is incomplete.

FINAL EXPECTATION:
- school Admin controls thier school system.
- Employees operate workflows.
- Students and parents receive meaningful, accurate data.
- The system feels authoritative, not decorative.

Proceed continuously until the system is fully operational.